  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nHot Dragon Chili Salad\nFood Info\n25\n-3\n10\nVeggie\nObject Info\nPerk\nIncreases temperature by 40 degrees for 5 minutes.\n15 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x2\nCan be Cooked only in Portable Crock Pot\n15 sec\n30\nMiscellaneous\n\"dragonchilisalad\"\n“I hope I can handle the spice level.”\n–Wilson\n“I can't wait to eat it.”\n–Willow\n“Vegetables help Wolfgang grow big and strong.”\n–Wolfgang\n“I missed having someone make me dinner...”\n–Wendy\n“MY MINIONS WILL SUSTAIN ME”\n–WX-78\n“I do like fresh greens.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Looks really good, buddy.”\n–Woodie\n“I permit him to stay so long as he keeps cooking.”\n–Maxwell\n“Yeuch! I was prömised a feast!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Okay, we'll eat a salad.”\n–Webber\n“A hint of spice to awaken the tastebuds.”\n–Warly\n“Eating bits”\n–Wormwood\n“Can't believe Warly's got me eatin' salads.”\n–Winona\n“Warly spends a lot of time on this stuff.”\n–Wortox\n“Mmmm, thank you fancy cook man!”\n–Wurt\n“Is it made from real dragons?”\n–Walter\n“Warly always finds such unique combinations.”\n–Wanda\nThe Hot Dragon Chili Salad is a Don't Starve Together and Warly specific Food item cooked in the Portable Crock Pot by combining one Dragon Fruit, one Pepper, and two fillers.\nUsing two Twigs as filler will result in Dragon Pie while using meat will result in Meatballs. Attempting to cook a Hot Dragon Chili Salad in a regular Crock Pot will result in Dragon Pie.\nConsuming a Hot Dragon Chili Salad keeps player temperature up to 40° above ambient temperature for 5 minutes. It does not make player immune to freezing effects from the Deerclops, Blue Hounds or Ice Staffs.\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\n×2\nFillers cannot be Meats, Eggs or Inedibles.\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×3\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
